Summary: Public API - Create Trym Integrator Key
Do not apply credits to $0.00 costing inventory when receiving
Release Notes:
The way credits and shipping charges are calculated have changed.

* When calculating credits to products on receiving, do not apply the credit to anything that has a $0.00 wholesale cost.
* When calculating credits to products on receiving, do not include a product in the distribution of credits if the credit will force the wholesale cost to go negative. Instead, evenly apply the credit to those products where subtracting the credit will not make the total cost of the product go negative.
* Ensure that there is a cap to the credit amount entered. The credits entered should be no more than the total costs of the receive.

Summary: Differentiate Between $0 and Blank Unit Costs
Release Notes:
We are now distinguishing a difference between a blank entry and a 0 entry in the ‚ÄòCost‚Äô field for products. The change will be in effect anywhere we record and show cost, including receiving, packages, products, and reporting. 

This change will allow users to record $0 costs, which will improve the accuracy of receiving, reporting, costing, and pricing. Users will now be able to tell the difference between an item with a $0 cost and an item with no cost at all. Additionally, an entry of ‚Äú0‚Äù will now be accepted in cost fields if the cost is ‚ÄòRequired' in field configuration.

Summary: Dutchie Pay - Get updated user account balances
Release Notes:
This release updates how we gather bank account balances for customer transactions.

Previously, we were not getting a fresh balance with each transaction. 

This update gets a fresh balance check when the customer completes their Ecomm order. If an additional order (or pickup of the original order) occurs within 2hrs, the balance is not updated (due to a current limitation on the MX side). If the pick-up or additional order occurs >2hrs, a fresh balance will be provided from MX.

Summary: Dutchie Pay | Improved Payment Error Codes
Release Notes:
Updates to error messaging that results from customers attempting to complete purchases using Dutchie Pay on Ecomm.

Error codes is included with each message. This error code can be used as a reference by both the customer and for support.

Support can develop scripts around each error code to provide the customer with additional details.

Summary: Create Location to Host POS File Upload
Release Notes:
Creates a new location in LLx called Superusers>Superuser Tools>Data Import:

* Implementation specialists can upload third-party POS export files in this location to start the process to map the export to the LLx data import schema, validate the customer data, and import the data into LLx. 
* Implementation specialists must enter the users state or province, the POS system used by the customer, and upload the POS export file to start the process.

Summary: Create New Permissions for Data Import
Release Notes:
Adds a permission for Superusers with Edit permissions. This feature provides the ability to enable access to new sub-menu item  in the in LLx Left-side navigation bar for Superusers:

* Super Users > Data Import

Superusers with Edit permissions have the ability to enable select implementation specialists access to the new Data Import page while a location is in Staging. 

* Data Import is permission-based for select Implementation Specialists
* Data Import is no longer available once the location is published and goes live (isLive = True)
* Data Import is blocked by a Super User Edit permission - it is visible only to those with access

Summary: Create New Permissions for Revert to Staging
Release Notes:
Adds a new permission for Superusers with Edit permissions. The permission provides the ability to enable select implementation specialists access to the new Revert to Staging feature on the Publish page. (The revert to staging feature allows a location to be reverted from published to staging and re-enables staging tools for the the location.)   

* Publish is permission-based for select Implementation Specialists
* Permission enables access to the Revert to Staging feature on Superusers > Publish
* Superuser with Edit permissions (such as Implementation Ops) grant access
* Access to the Publish page and the Revert to Staging feature is available after location is published (isLive = True) to Superusers with this permission
* The Revert to Staging feature is blocked by a Super User Edit permission - it is visible only to those with access

Summary: Define, Document & Implement Naming Conventions for  Staging Phase
Release Notes:
This story creates a naming convention for new locations during the onboarding process for customers. New customer locations will automatically default to staging (isLive = False) now rather than to production as the current process provides. A new naming convention for these staging locations is required so everyone can clearly identify a location in this phase. 

* If a location isLive = False, the tag ‚ÄúStaging‚Äù is appended to end of location name at creation
* When a location is published (isLive = True), the tag is removed from the location name
